<div1 type="letter" n="1943-07-23">
<head>Postcard from Gustaf E. Lambert to Albert E. Truby, July 23, [1943]</head>
<pb n="1" id="f06401126"/>
<opener>
<dateline>
<date value="1943-07-23">1943 July 23<hi rend="superscript">rd</hi></date>
</dateline>
<salute>Dear Sir</salute>
</opener>
<p>Book came today will start<lb/>
reading to night when through<lb/>
with my work, &ldquo;Thanks a million&rdquo;<lb/>
one more of guinea pigs have<lb/>
passed away Clyde L. West died<lb/>
July 16 <hi rend="superscript">th</hi> only 3 of my old patients<lb/>
left <hi>4 if Forbes is alive</hi> Respt.</p>
<p>(No record of Spaniards)</p>
<closer>
<signed>Gust E Lambert</signed>
</closer>
</div1>
</body>
